msgid "How to edit the documentation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/how-to-edit-the-rst-documentation.rst:5
#: 8824b16cc7cc49998d042bab82a32ac3
msgid "The Qubes OS documentation is stored as `reStructuredText (rST) <https://docutils.sourceforge.io/rst.html>`__ files in the `qubes-doc <https://github.com/QubesOS/qubes-doc>`__ repository."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/how-to-edit-the-rst-documentation.rst:8
#: 036c2fc3bcad456aa11d690905799e69
msgid "We use `Sphinx <https://www.sphinx-doc.org/>`__ for building and `Read The Docs (RTD) <https://readthedocs.com/>`__ for hosting. RTD is a `continuous‑documentation deployment platform <https://docs.readthedocs.com/platform/stable/continuous-deployment.html>`__ that can automatically detect changes in a GitHub repository and build the latest version of a documentation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/how-to-edit-the-rst-documentation.rst:13
#: 3e62724992754ec395310d313010e13d
msgid "Qubes OS Documentation Workflow - once new documentation is written or changed, it is built and verified with Sphinx, pushed on GitHub/GitLab and hosted on RTD"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/how-to-edit-the-rst-documentation.rst:19
#: e11009abd745456d8dcbc403ab582905
msgid "By cloning and regularly pulling from `qubes-doc <https://github.com/QubesOS/qubes-doc>`__ repository, users can maintain their own up-to-date offline copy of the Qubes documentation rather than relying solely on the web and either serve it locally or read the rST files directly. EPUB or PDF versions of Qubes OS documentation can also be downloaded from `doc.qubes-os.org <https://doc.qubes-os.org/en/latest/>`__:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/how-to-edit-the-rst-documentation.rst:25
#: 78714f6affb94847af45cfe27b4cf29e
msgid "Highlights from where one can download a ePUB or PDF of hte Qubes OS documentation deployed on RTD"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/how-to-edit-the-rst-documentation.rst:31
#: 8428b8f6547b45fa9738d9a1097a9d47
msgid "The documentation is a volunteer community effort. People like you are constantly working to make it better. If you notice something that can be fixed or improved, please follow the steps below to open a pull request!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/how-to-edit-the-rst-documentation.rst:38
#: df1ece079ab14c3a85f03329333e5ce0
msgid "How to submit a pull request"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/how-to-edit-the-rst-documentation.rst:40
#: 91e89d0b351748aaa51e289c4d81af34
msgid "We keep all the rST documentation in `qubes-doc <https://github.com/QubesOS/qubes-doc>`__, a dedicated Git repository hosted on `GitHub <https://github.com/>`__. Thanks to GitHub’s easy web interface, you can edit the documentation even if you’re not familiar with Git or the command line! All you need is a free GitHub account."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/how-to-edit-the-rst-documentation.rst:46
#: 12cf32f87f874ee99ed7edd5df53661f
msgid "A few notes before we get started:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/how-to-edit-the-rst-documentation.rst:48
#: 2f96e68f2fef4161bc3d8d659ecddb00
msgid "Since Qubes is a security-oriented project, every documentation change will be :ref:`reviewed <developer/general/how-to-edit-the-rst-documentation:security>` before it’s accepted. This allows us to maintain quality control and protect our users."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/how-to-edit-the-rst-documentation.rst:50
#: 0d1c2d9191e342ea95aacd2e1c43b536
msgid "To give your contribution a better chance of being accepted, please follow our :doc:`/developer/general/rst-documentation-style-guide`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/how-to-edit-the-rst-documentation.rst:52
#: e5f6d97f0e4541eb8aa6f56efded047e
msgid "We don’t want you to spend time and effort on a contribution that we can’t accept. If your contribution would take a lot of time, please :doc:`file an issue </introduction/issue-tracking>` for it first so that we can make sure we’re on the same page before significant works begins."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/how-to-edit-the-rst-documentation.rst:54
#: 1f042312b299453b91438193510082e3
msgid "Alternatively, you may already have written content that doesn’t conform to these guidelines, but you’d be willing to modify it so that it does. In this case, you can still submit it by following the instructions below. Just make a note in your pull request (PR) that you’re aware of the changes that need to be made and that you’re just asking for the content to be reviewed before you spend time making those changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/how-to-edit-the-rst-documentation.rst:56
#: b2109ad830814cdfab0d298a4c435b51
msgid "Finally, if you’ve written something that doesn’t belong in qubes-doc but that would be beneficial to the Qubes community, please consider adding it to the :ref:`external documentation <developer/general/rst-documentation-style-guide:core vs. external documentation>`."
msgstr ""

